## 3. Content Rules\
\
### 3.1 Topic placeholder (EN)\
\
- Use **"the feeling"** as the topic-agnostic placeholder.\
- Do **not** replace it with a specific topic (e.g. "anxiety", "stress") in the canonical EN source.\
\
### 3.2 Topic placeholder (zh_tw)\
\
- Use **one consistent placeholder** for "the feeling" across all zh_tw content (e.g. **\uc0\u37027 \u31278 \u24863 \u21463 ** or **\u36889 \u31278 \u24863 \u21463 **). Document the choice in the project glossary.\
- **Never** use \uc0\u28966 \u34385 , \u32202 \u24373 , or any specific diagnosis/topic as the default translation of "the feeling."\
- Topic-specific wording is allowed only where the EN source explicitly names a topic.\
\
### 3.3 Forbidden in content\
\
- 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 [INTAKE INCOMPLETE]
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 TODO
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 TRANSLATE LATER
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- Any other stub or placeholder that is not final reader-facing copy.\
\
### 3.4 YAML safety (if editing per-variant YAML by hand)\
\
- Content often contains colons (
\f7\fs28 \cb9 :
\f0\fs32 \cb7 ) and newlines. To avoid parse errors:\
  - **Preferred:** Store 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 content
\f0\fs32 \cb7  as a **single double-quoted string** with 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 \\n
\f0\fs32 \cb7  for newlines (e.g. 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 content: "First line.\\n\\nSecond para."
\f0\fs32 \cb7 ).\
  - **Alternative:** Use a YAML literal block (
\f7\fs28 \cb9 |
\f0\fs32 \cb7 ) with consistent indentation; ensure no line starts with a word followed by 
\f7\fs28 \cb9 : 
\f0\fs32 \cb7  or the parser will treat it as a key.\
- Running the export script from the registry produces valid YAML automatically; hand-editing is error-prone.\
