\fs32 \cf0 \cb7 EU language translations \'96 status\
What EU locales have (pre\uc0\u8209 V4 / legacy)\
All 10 EU locales in the locale registry have content under SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/\{locale\}/:\
Locale	Content present\
de_de, fr_fr, es_es, it_it, pt_pt, nl_nl, pl_pl, sv_se, da_dk, fi_fi	\uc0\u9989  Same set of files in each\
Files in each EU locale dir:\
a0_a1_conclusion_translations.csv\
ab_chapter_vars.csv\
exercise_translations.csv\
format_wrappers.yaml\
gen_alpha_students_opinion_* and gen_z_professionals_opinion_* CSVs\
script_vars.csv\
somatic_generic_with_10_styles.csv\
So EU languages do have translations for: A0/A1 conclusion, chapter vars, exercises, format wrappers, opinion styles, script vars, somatic content.\
They are registered in SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/registry.yaml (de-DE, fr-FR, es-ES, it-IT, pt-PT, nl-NL, pl-PL, sv-SE, da-DK, fi-FI).\
What EU locales do not have (Omega V4 sections)\
None of the EU locales have Omega V4 section content:\
No phoenix_v4/libraries/sections/ under SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/\{locale\}/\
No registry.yaml for V4 sections\
No per\uc0\u8209 variant YAMLs (chapter_XX/section_YY_type/.yaml)\
So for V4 section content (the 12\uc0\u8209 chapter book body), only EN (and zh_tw) have a full V4 section tree. EU locales do not.\
How V4 assembly behaves for EU today\
The assembler resolves the sections root by locale:\
SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/\{locale\}/phoenix_v4/libraries/sections\
For de_de, fr_fr, etc., that path does not exist.\
So for a plan with e.g. locale: de_de, the assembler falls back to the EN sections root and uses English section content for the book body.\
EU translations in the locale dirs (CSVs, format_wrappers, etc.) are still used where the rest of the pipeline reads from SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/\{locale\}/ (e.g. chapter angle/integration, A0/A1, exercises), but not for the V4 section registry/per\uc0\u8209 variant content, because that doesn\'92t exist for EU yet.\
Summary\
Layer	EU status\
Locale registry	\uc0\u9989  10 EU locales registered\
Legacy / pre\uc0\u8209 V4 (A0/A1, chapter vars, exercises, format wrappers, opinion, script vars, somatic)	\u9989  Translated and present per locale\
Omega V4 sections (registry + per\uc0\u8209 variant YAMLs)	\u10060  Not present; only EN and zh_tw have V4 section content\
So: EU language translations exist for the legacy/pre\uc0\u8209 V4 content and are in use where that content is referenced. For the V4 system (full book sections), EU is not translated yet; any new EU V4 intake would need to follow docs/V4_LOCALE_INTAKE_CONTRACT.md (and the writer spec) and add SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/locale/\{locale\}/phoenix_v4/libraries/sections/ with registry and exported per\u8209 variant YAMLs.\cb1 \
